Description: Find number.  14 digits in total, consisting of four digit project code (location) frollowed by a '.'.  Then a 5 digit number, followed by the three digit category code, followed by a 3 digit number.  In some cases there is a '-'- followed by a two digit number.
Project code (Location).  NZC1 (Ferdinand Bolstraat), NZD1 (Damrak), NZDAM1 (Bijenkorf), NZN1 (Nieuwe Leeuwarderweg), NZR1 (Rokin), NZR2 (Rokin), NZS1 (Stationsplein), NZV1 (Vijzelgrach)

Material category (25 different catagories: ---, BWM (Buildings and Structures), CER (Ceramic), CPY (Consumption), FAU (Faunal remains), GLS (Glass), HK (unknown), HT (combined metal and wood), KHL, KSC, KST, LEE, MA, MHT, MIX, MSC, MTL, PLT, SC, SLK, STN, TW, TXT, VST, XXX
Fits or belongs to find number(s)
Hilted weapons: Total length in mm
Building material: Greatest length in mm
Building material: Greatest width in mm
Building material: Greatest thickness in mm
Knives: Whittle tang or scale tang
Natural stone: Greatest length in mm
Natural stone: Greatest width in mm
Natural stone: Greatest height in mm
Natural stone: Greatest thickness in mm
Pipes: Mark on side of bowl - left
Pipes: Mark on side of bowl - right
Pipes: Mark on base of heel - left
Pipes: Mark on base of heel - right
